<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Estimation_theory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> The sample maximum is never more than the population maximum, but can be less, hence it is a <a href="/wiki/Biased_estimator" title="Biased estimator" class="mw-redirect">biased estimator</a>: it will tend to <i>underestimate</i> the population maximum.</li>
</ol>
</div>
